{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Momardi","author":"Tuesday Gutierrez"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"5fb8b613-6c7a-5596-ade4-3d0fd250ef1b","excerpt":"The more our lives become intertwined with technology, the more the  Kinetica Art Fair  becomes a relevant platform for ambitious tech…","html":"<p>The more our lives become intertwined with technology, the more the <a href=\"http://www.kinetica-artfair.com/\">Kinetica Art Fair</a> becomes a relevant platform for ambitious tech-related type of art. Now on its fifth year, <strong>Kinetica Art Fair is bustling with energy and possibilities.</strong> The great thing about the Kinetic Art Fair is that it looks to the future and yes, it’s future is oh so bright.  I predict that in a few years to come, it will become a much more important exhibition and would garner more funding from not just new media outfits but also by top art ponchos.</p>\n<p>A convergence of kinetic, electronic, robotic, sound, light, time-based and multi-disciplinary new media art, Kinetica Art Fair brings artworks from more than <strong>35 galleries and some of the artists featured are with international pedigree</strong>. It’s not surprising that this is not a curated art fair.  Art is for all and so is technology although I am sure that if it is curated better, it can be a formidable force in the arts world. But for now, here in the Kinetica Art Fair, there is a sense of <strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">collaborative spirit all happening between artists, designers, architects and new media students</span></strong> so much so that it seems like they are breeding this into their own playground.</p>\n<p>Interactivity is in the heart of the Kinetica Art Fair: from a typewriter that beats drum sounds into bottles to a large-scale sculptural zoetrope, there are unexpected things in this exhibition that can take your breath away.</p>\n<p><strong>1. A sculptural dream-world</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"youtube\"><div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/OIHxjqZ7pTU?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div></iframe></span><br>\n<em><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Gregory Barsamian at Kinetica Art Fair 2013</span><br>\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\">A modernisation of the Zoetrope, inspired by Carl Jung<br>\n</span></em></p>\n<p><strong>2. 3d but 2d</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"youtube\"><div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/GPOtykKvTFI?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div></iframe></span><br>\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>The Trulife™ Hologram reproduces the same light wave which reflected off the original object *created by [<span style=\"color: #888888;\"></em>Colour Holographic*</span>](<a href=\"http://www.colourholographic.com/\">http://www.colourholographic.com/</a>)</span></p>\n<p><strong>3. Tech Ocean</strong></p>\n<p> <span class=\"youtube\"><div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/vAlrnRrrVpw?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div></iframe></span><br>\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>The Mechanical Ocean Wave Simulator, Ciboure 2013 by <a href=\"http://www.kinetica-artfair.com/?exhibitors/2013?cat=5\"><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Matthieu Schönholzer</span></a></em></span><br>\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>One of the pioneers of 3d-FX computer graphics industry, this is Matthieu’s foray into the world of interactive sculpture</em></span></p>\n<p>** 4. Fibre optic figure**</p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/seated-child_roselin-de-thelin_jmnbdz.jpg\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"seated child_roselin de thelin\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/5c7891e023a2384e0f2f36f3f8346d66/8c020/seated-child_roselin-de-thelin_jmnbdz.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/5c7891e023a2384e0f2f36f3f8346d66/da4c4/seated-child_roselin-de-thelin_jmnbdz.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/5c7891e023a2384e0f2f36f3f8346d66/37caf/seated-child_roselin-de-thelin_jmnbdz.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/5c7891e023a2384e0f2f36f3f8346d66/8c020/seated-child_roselin-de-thelin_jmnbdz.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/5c7891e023a2384e0f2f36f3f8346d66/ec4bb/seated-child_roselin-de-thelin_jmnbdz.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </a><em><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Seated Child (Columba) by Roseline de Thelin</span></em><br>\n<span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>Roselin used fibre optics to create light points to create an illusion of a seated figure</em></span></p>\n<p>** 5. Type some sounds**</p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/xiaofei-dyson_rrfqhm.jpg\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"xiaofei dyson\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/115362e7edcf41d03e670f63f4006e8c/8c020/xiaofei-dyson_rrfqhm.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/115362e7edcf41d03e670f63f4006e8c/da4c4/xiaofei-dyson_rrfqhm.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/115362e7edcf41d03e670f63f4006e8c/37caf/xiaofei-dyson_rrfqhm.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/115362e7edcf41d03e670f63f4006e8c/8c020/xiaofei-dyson_rrfqhm.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/115362e7edcf41d03e670f63f4006e8c/ec4bb/xiaofei-dyson_rrfqhm.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </a><span style=\"color: #888888;\">*A typewriter that drums bottles by Xiaofei Dyson – an interactive installation that invites young and adults to play *</span></p>\n<p>** 6. Flipping books**</p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/mechanical-flipbook_wendy-marvel_by9bw4.jpg\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"mechanical flipbook_wendy marvel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/1d645e0ae51d1d6f6bc32e302dff214d/8c020/mechanical-flipbook_wendy-marvel_by9bw4.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/1d645e0ae51d1d6f6bc32e302dff214d/da4c4/mechanical-flipbook_wendy-marvel_by9bw4.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/1d645e0ae51d1d6f6bc32e302dff214d/37caf/mechanical-flipbook_wendy-marvel_by9bw4.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/1d645e0ae51d1d6f6bc32e302dff214d/8c020/mechanical-flipbook_wendy-marvel_by9bw4.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/1d645e0ae51d1d6f6bc32e302dff214d/ec4bb/mechanical-flipbook_wendy-marvel_by9bw4.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </a><span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>Mechanical Flipbook – created by Wendy Marvel and Mark Rosen. Made from Hand Machined parts from Bronze, Aluminum, Steel and 50’s era Aircraft Chassis Boxes</em></span></p>\n<p><strong>7. Keyboard beauty</strong></p>\n<p> <a href=\"./images/alexander-berchert_d6upd7.jpg\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"alexander berchert\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/378388a8431eec5c5967b23440cca046/8c020/alexander-berchert_d6upd7.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/378388a8431eec5c5967b23440cca046/da4c4/alexander-berchert_d6upd7.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/378388a8431eec5c5967b23440cca046/37caf/alexander-berchert_d6upd7.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/378388a8431eec5c5967b23440cca046/8c020/alexander-berchert_d6upd7.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/378388a8431eec5c5967b23440cca046/ec4bb/alexander-berchert_d6upd7.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </a><span style=\"color: #888888;\"><em>Alexander Berchert creates this artwork combining his fascination for mass-produced objects and physics</em></span></p>\n<p><strong>8. Breathing H20</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/breathe_ben-tyers_tn2rcd.jpg\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"breathe_ben tyers\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/674b868883101cd5e3f6baafbe14a799/8c020/breathe_ben-tyers_tn2rcd.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/674b868883101cd5e3f6baafbe14a799/da4c4/breathe_ben-tyers_tn2rcd.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/674b868883101cd5e3f6baafbe14a799/37caf/breathe_ben-tyers_tn2rcd.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/674b868883101cd5e3f6baafbe14a799/8c020/breathe_ben-tyers_tn2rcd.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/674b868883101cd5e3f6baafbe14a799/ec4bb/breathe_ben-tyers_tn2rcd.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </a><em><span style=\"color: #888888;\">Breathe by Ben Tyers. A water container that emulates the act of breathing.</span></em></p>\n<p><strong>9. Fishing line but not for fish</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/08015_david-ogle_shcl9d.jpg\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"08015_david ogle\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/1ecfe7121659fff6df30e3977c0aa96a/8c020/08015_david-ogle_shcl9d.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/1ecfe7121659fff6df30e3977c0aa96a/da4c4/08015_david-ogle_shcl9d.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/1ecfe7121659fff6df30e3977c0aa96a/37caf/08015_david-ogle_shcl9d.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/1ecfe7121659fff6df30e3977c0aa96a/8c020/08015_david-ogle_shcl9d.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/1ecfe7121659fff6df30e3977c0aa96a/ec4bb/08015_david-ogle_shcl9d.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </a><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>08015 by David Ogle – made from fluorescent fishing line and ultraviolet light</em></span>. <span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>David explores the notions of materiality, of permanence and the visual perceptions of object in space.</em></span></p>\n<p><strong>10. Tech fingers</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"./images/bailey-bots_marko-kryut_fadvxt.jpg\">\n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 630px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 79.6875%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"bailey bots_marko kryut\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/momardi/static/9944e39ab2949dade84d7142abd88729/8c020/bailey-bots_marko-kryut_fadvxt.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/momardi/static/9944e39ab2949dade84d7142abd88729/da4c4/bailey-bots_marko-kryut_fadvxt.jpg 158w,\n/momardi/static/9944e39ab2949dade84d7142abd88729/37caf/bailey-bots_marko-kryut_fadvxt.jpg 315w,\n/momardi/static/9944e39ab2949dade84d7142abd88729/8c020/bailey-bots_marko-kryut_fadvxt.jpg 630w,\n/momardi/static/9944e39ab2949dade84d7142abd88729/ec4bb/bailey-bots_marko-kryut_fadvxt.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </a><span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>Bailey Bots by Marko Kryut – two moving robotic hands exploring the origins of matter</em></span></p>\n<p>Read more:<br>\n<a href=\"http://www.culture24.org.uk/art/sculpture%20%26%20installation/art422490\">Wunderkammeras and techno-animalism: Kinetica Art Fair returns to Ambika P3 –  Culture 24</a><br>\n<a href=\"http://www.newscientist.com/blogs/culturelab/2013/03/kinetica-artfair.html\">Kinetica comes into its own illusory adventures – New Scientist blog</a><br>\n<a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/03/01/kinetica-2013-art-fair_n_2789402.html?utm_hp_ref=uk\">When Art and Science Collide (Pictures) – Huffington Post</a><br>\n<a href=\"http://www.artlyst.com/articles/kinetica-art-fair-2013-half-matrix-half-diagon-alley\">Kinetica Art Fair – Half Matrix – Half Diagon Alley – Artlyst</a></p>\n<p><span class=\"youtube\"><div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 78.90625%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe allowfullscreen class=\"youtube-player\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/eqNRrUDSI8Y?wmode=transparent&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;iv_load_policy=3&amp;showsearch=0&amp;rel=0&amp;theme=dark\" title=\"YouTube video player\" type=\"text/html\" style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div></iframe></span><br>\n<span style=\"color: #808080;\"><em>More on Kinetic Art Fair 2013</em></span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"(My Top Ten Picks) Kinetica Art Fair: The Future of Art and Technology","date":"March 01, 2013"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2013-03-01---kinetica-art-fair-the-future-of-art-and-technology/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2013-01-26---interview-with-artist-louise-champion-painting-the-mundane/"},"frontmatter":